name: SpeedRunners
description: Cut-throat multiplayer running game that pits 4 players against each other, locally and/or online. Run, jump, swing around, and use devious weapons and pick-ups to knock opponents off-screen! One of the most competitive games you'll ever play.

name: Move or Die
description: Official Move Or Die Discord bot!

name: Holodrive
description: Holodrive is a super fast-paced collectable 2D multiplayer shooter. Create your robot, customize it and jetpack your way to victory!

name: GRIP
description: GRIP - return of the Combat Racer!

name: Hellion
description: Hellion is a first person multiplayer space survival game. It is a fusion of survival and space simulation genres that pits players against the deadly environment and one another. Survive the hard vacuum, extreme temperatures, deadly radiation and scavenge for basic resources like air, water, and other items necessary for survival.

name: Divinity Original Sin 2
description: Divinity: Original Sin 2 is a CRPG developed by Larian Studios. Setting: The world needs a new Divinity. Choose your origin. Gather your party. Master deep, tactical combat. Up to four players with drop-in/drop-out co-op. Only one becomes a God.

name: Foxhole
description: Foxhole Description

name: Unturned
description: You're a survivor in the zombie infested ruins of society, and must work with your friends and forge alliances to remain among the living.

name: League of Legends
description: A free-to-play competitive MOBA game with a large following in eSports. From the original developers of DotA: Allstars, the game expands the gameplay found in DotA by adding persistent Summoner profiles and a variety of original champions who fight for you on the battlefield against bots or one another.

name: PLAYERUNKNOWN'S BATTLEGROUNDS
description: Led by the modder behind the Battle Royale mods for the ArmA series, PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds is a shooter that pits 100 players in a large empty location where they must scavenge for weapons and fight to the death.

name: Overwatch
description: A stylish sci-fi, team-based, first-person shooter from Blizzard in which players can choose from a wide range of Heroes with unique weapons and abilities.

name: Minecraft
description: A procedurally-generated game of world exploration, resource harvesting, and freeform construction. It supports local and online multiplayer, and is regularly updated with new content and features.

name: World of Warcraft
description: World of Warcraft is an MMORPG that takes place in Blizzard Entertainment's Warcraft universe; at its peak, it boasted a player base of over 12.5 million subscribers, making it the most popular MMO of all time.

name: Hearthstone
description: A Free-to-Play collectible card game by Blizzard Entertainment set in the Warcraft universe.

name: Dota 2
description: The official free-to-play sequel to the Warcraft III custom scenario that originally popularized the Multiplayer Online Battle Arena sub-genre.

name: Tom Clancy's Rainbow Six Siege
description: A first-person tactical shooter developed by Ubisoft Montreal Studios. In this installment of the Rainbow Six series, some players are focused on assault where as others are defense-oriented.

name: Rocket League
description: The sequel to Supersonic Acrobatic Rocket-Powered Battle-Cars, Rocket League is the second vehicular sports-action game developed by Psyonix.

name: Heroes of the Storm
description: Heroes from Warcraft, StarCraft, Diablo, Overwatch, and other universes are summoned to the Nexus for five-on-five combat in Blizzard's take on the MOBA genre.

name: Garry's Mod
description: Build stuff. Destroy stuff. Spawn so many dominoes that the server crashes with a "no free edicts" error. Such is life in Garry's Mod.

name: H1Z1: King of the Kill
description: Originally a separate PVP mode of the open-world survival-horror shooter now known as "Just Survive", H1Z1 pits upwards to 150 players in a large empty island to scavenge for gear and fight to the death. It was later made free-to-play.

name: ARK: Survival Evolved
description: A multiplayer first-person survival game set in a world populated by dinosaurs.

name: Paladins
description: Paladins is a multiplayer arena shooter from Hi-Rez Studios (Tribes Ascend, Smite).

name: Path of Exile
description: Path of Exile is a free-to-play PC online action Role-Playing Game set in a dark fantasy world.

name: Team Fortress 2
description: The long-awaited sequel to the class-based first-person shooter Team Fortress Classic sports a unique cartoony visual style, more accessible gameplay, and a very large amount of updates and new features since its original release.

name: Rust
description: From the makers of Garry's Mod, Rust is a multiplayer survival game with combat elements.

name: World of Tanks
description: World of Tanks is a free-to-play (F2P) massively multiplayer online (MMO) team based action game featuring WWII era tank combat.

name: FINAL FANTASY XIV
aliases: FINAL FANTASY XIV - A Realm Reborn
description: Stormblood is the second expansion to Final Fantasy XIV

name: Geometry Dash
description: Control a cube, and avoid the pointy obstacles by listening and jumping on the rhythm of the soundtrack.

name: Dolphin
description: An Atari 2600 game where players controls a dolphin who must use echolocation to avoid obstacles and escape from a pursuing octopus.

name: Terraria
description: The first major 2D entry into the world of "open world" sandbox action-adventure games, Terraria is inspired by 16-bit platformers and allows players to mine for ores, craft new equipment, and fight monstrous bosses in a large procedurally-generated world.

name: Brawlhalla
description: Brawlhalla is an 8-player, 2D fighting game featuring warriors from throughout history.

name: The Walking Dead
description: Starbreeze's Overkill is developing a new co-op focused game set in the Walking Dead universe.

name: Sonic Mania
description: An official throwback to the early-'90s Sega Genesis roots of the Sonic the Hedgehog series from some notable creators of the series's fanwork.

name: Golf With Your Friends
description: Online multiplayer minigolf game from Blacklight Interactive.

name: Cities: Skylines
description: Cities: Skylines is a city-building simulation heavily inspired by the SimCity franchise.

name: Arma 3
description: Arma 3 is the third core game in the simulation and modern combat Arma franchise developed by Bohemia Interactive.

name: Left 4 Dead 2
description: In the sequel to Valve's cooperative zombie shooter, a new team of four ragtag survivors must work together to survive the apocalypse, facing new Infected threats as they fight their way across the Southern United States.

name: RuneScape
description: RuneScape is a popular browser based MMORPG with large amounts of content for both free-to-play and pay-to-play users.

name: Dead by Daylight
description: Four survivors try to escape a variety of haunted locales, but a supernatural being that feeds on their hope sends a serial murderer to hunt them down in this asymmetrical multiplayer survival-horror game.

name: War Thunder
description: War Thunder is a free-to-play air combat game set in the World War II and Korean War eras. Naval and land battles are planned additions.

name: Battlefield 1
description: The long-running Battlefield series goes even further back in time in the 15th installment, this time to the first World War.

name: The Binding of Isaac: Rebirth
description: An enhanced remake of the original Binding of Isaac that features expanded gameplay, pixel art visuals, and a variety of other new additions - including full controller support and local asymmetric co-op.

name: Black Desert Online
description: A sandbox action MMORPG.

name: Black Squad
description: Black Squad is a free-to-play, military-themed First Person Shooter developed by NS Studio.

name: HIVESWAP: ACT 1
description: Hiveswap: Act 1 is a point-and-click adventure game

name: Hearts of Iron IV
description: The next entry in the series of WWII wargames from Paradox Interactive.

name: Blade & Soul
description: Blade & Soul is a MMORPG currently in development by NCsoft's Team Bloodlust development team. The characters in this oriental style game are designed by the well-known illustrator Hyung-tae Kim.

name: Sid Meier's Civilization V
description: Civilization V brings brand new gameplay elements to this beloved franchise, while maintaining the "just one more turn" mentality.

name: SMITE
description: A free-to-play MOBA game from the developers of Global Agenda and Tribes Ascend. Smite is played entirely in third person and every spell and attack is a skillshot.

name: Factorio
description: A game about building factories on an alien planet.

name: Diablo III
description: Diablo III returns to the world of Sanctuary twenty years after the events of Diablo II with a new generation of heroes that must defeat the demonic threat from Hell.

name: StarCraft II
description: Legacy of the Void is the third and final part of the StarCraft II trilogy, coming in the form of a standalone game. It follows the blueprint of the other two parts of StarCraft II but this time focuses on the Protoss and the mysterious Xel'Naga.

name: The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim
description: The fifth installment in Bethesda's Elder Scrolls franchise is set in the eponymous province of Skyrim, where the ancient threat of dragons, led by the sinister Alduin, is rising again to threaten all mortal races. Only the player, as the prophesied hero the Dovahkiin, can save the world from destruction.

name: Tom Clancy's The Division
description: An online-only open-world shooter-RPG from Ubisoft Massive set in a chaotic New York City that is wrought by disease.

name: Don't Starve Together
description: Don't Starve Together is the standalone multiplayer expansion of the uncompromising survival game Don't Starve.

name: ShellShock Live
description: An online multiplayer artillery game that pits players against each other in team or free-for-all matches with a huge variety of weapons.

name: Space Engineers
description: A sandbox space game focused on fun and building.

name: Euro Truck Simulator 2
description: Travel across Europe as a trucker delivering cargo in a variety of trucks.

name: Portal 2
description: Portal 2 is the sequel to the acclaimed first-person puzzle game, carrying forward its love of mind-bending problems and its reckless disregard for the space-time continuum.

name: The Sims 4
description: The fourth installment of the main Sims franchise, revamping the series's customization features while improving the Sims' automations and emotions.

name: Call of Duty: Black Ops III
description: Set 40 years after the events of Black Ops II, the twelfth installment of the Call of Duty series brings advanced robotics and biotic augmentations to the clandestine operations of the Black Ops storyline.

name: Stardew Valley
description: An open-ended country-life RPG in which players can manage their own farm and interact with the surrounding community.

name: DARK SOULS III
description: This game melds elements from all previous Souls games and concludes the Dark Souls trilogy.

name: Counter-Strike: Source
description: Counter-Strike gets reborn with a shiny new game engine in this 2004 remake.

name: Fallout 4
description: The Fallout series continues in a post-apocalyptic Boston, Massachusetts.

name: Fallout: New Vegas
description: The post-apocalyptic Fallout universe expands into Nevada in this new title in the franchise. As a courier once left for dead by a mysterious man in a striped suit, the player must now set out to find his assailant and uncover the secrets of the enigmatic ruler of New Vegas.

name: MapleStory
description: The worlds first side-scrolling massively multiplayer online role-playing game

name: The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt
aliases: The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt - Game of the Year Edition

publishers.name: CD Projekt RED Sp. z o.o.

developers.name: CD Projekt RED Sp. z o.o.

description: CD Projekt RED's third Witcher combines the series' non-linear storytelling with a sprawling open world that concludes the saga of Geralt of Rivia.

name: Half-Life 2
description: Several years after the Black Mesa disaster, Gordon Freeman awakens from stasis to aid a resistance movement against the Combine, a collective of trans-dimensional aliens that have conquered Earth.

name: Battlefield 4
description: DICE's popular multiplayer-focused shooter series continues, making its debut appearance on the PS4 and Xbox One.

name: XCOM 2
description: The aliens have won and the remnants of XCOM must strike to take back the Earth in this sequel to Firaxis' 2012 reboot.

name: Guild Wars 2
description: Guild Wars 2 is an online RPG developed by ArenaNet, and continues the subscriptionless business model of the original Guild Wars. The game is set about 250 years after the events of its predecessor in a world devastated by the ancient elder dragons resurfacing after millennia of slumber.

name: The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim Special Edition
aliases: The Elder Scrolls V Skyrim Special Edition

name: Tooth and Tail
description: Lead the revolution with an army of flamethrowing Boars, mustard gas-lobbing Skunks, and paratrooper-puking Owls. Tooth and Tail is a Real-Time-Strategy game featuring Single Player, Online Competitive Play, Split Screen, Replays, and more. Build a base, lead your army, eat your enemies!

name: Outlast
description: Deep within the abandoned halls of Mount Massive Asylum, amateur journalist Miles Upshur sets out to find a good story, and instead finds an evil presence.

name: Depth
description: Depth is a multiplayer game which blends heart pounding tension and visceral action in a dark aquatic world.

name: Tabletop Simulator
description: A physics-based sandbox game that allows players to set up and play an endless variety of tabletop games. Along with numerous built-in games and DLC game packs (of actual licensed tabletop games), the game allows players to use custom boards, cards, miniatures, dice, and other objects from the Steam Workshop. Or they could make a mess and flip the whole table.

name: Stellaris
description: A sci-fi grand strategy game set in a procedurally generated universe from the creators of Crusader Kings and Europa Universalis.

name: Trove
description: Trove is a voxel based game from Trion Worlds, creators of Rift and Defiance.

name: Gang Beasts
description: Two to eight players punch, kick, and throw each other to be the last one standing in this physics-based brawler.

name: The Forest
description: Gather resources and build defenses in this first-person open-world survival horror game from indie studio Endnight Games.

name: Insurgency
description: Insurgency (originally Insurgency 2) is a multiplayer-focused first-person shooter with a focus on realism. It is based on the hit Half-Life mod of the same name.

name: Europa Universalis IV
description: The newest game in Paradox Interactive's grand strategy franchise, focusing on Europe in the Age of Discovery.

name: Town of Salem
description: A browser-based multiplayer strategy game based on the Salem witch trials, and inspired by party games like Mafia. 7 to 15 players are randomly and secretly divided into factions, and must determine each other's identities or prevent others from finding their own.

name: Robocraft
description: Robocraft is a competitive multiplayer shooter in which players build their own robots and pit them against each other. Crates earned after each match contain parts that can be used in future builds.

name: Golf It!
description: Golf It! is a multiplayer Minigolf game with a multiplayer Editor.

name: Heroes & Generals
description: From Reto-Moto, a company created by former Hitman developers, comes Heroes & Generals. A massively multiplayer online WW2 FPS.

name: Shadowverse
description: A popular mobile collectible card game now also on PC.

name: 7 Days to Die
description: 7 Days to Die is a voxel-based, open world sandbox survival game.

name: Killing Floor 2
description: The direct sequel to Tripwire's earlier wave-based horror FPS, Killing Floor 2 brings the fighting to the continental Europe with new heroes, monsters, and weapons.

name: StarCraft
description: StarCraft has been called the greatest real-time strategy game ever and it's certainly one of the most critically acclaimed. StarCraft features three powerful, yet balanced races: the Terrans, the Zerg, and the Protoss. You play as each race fights to the death for the fate of the universe.

name: Undertale
description: A quirky role-playing game that takes place in a secret subterranean world of monsters and gives players the choice to either kill or spare their enemies.

name: Dirty Bomb
description: Currently in open beta, Dirty Bomb is a class-based multiplayer PC game. It was previously known as Extraction.

name: Business Tour - Online Multiplayer Board Game
Fallout Shelter
description: A vault management simulator from Bethesda, set in the Fallout universe.

name: Slime Rancher
description: A vividly coloured and light-hearted game about building a ranch of slime creatures on another planet.

name: Last Man Standing
description: Last Man Standing

name: Titanfall 2
description: The sequel to Respawn's sci-fi mech-filled first-person shooter, Titanfall 2 adds a deep single-player campaign and revamped multiplayer.

name: STAR WARS Battlefront
description: The reboot to the Battlefront games of the PS2/Xbox era. Developed by DICE and published by EA.

name: Mount & Blade: Warband
description: Warband is a stand-alone expansion for Mount and Blade. It serves an improved and expanded re-release of the original Mount and Blade, a medieval open world RPG by Taleworlds.

name: STAR WARS: The Old Republic
description: Star Wars: The Old Republic is a massively-multiplayer role-playing game set 300 years after the events of BioWare's Knights of the Old Republic series, but still approximately 3,600 years before the events of the films.

name: PlanetSide 2
description: PlanetSide 2 is the sequel to the 2003 MMOFPS PlanetSide from Sony Online Entertainment which remains one of the most notable and successful games in the genre.

name: Clicker Heroes
description: A Free-to-Play Idle RPG where damage is determined by how fast the mouse button is clicked.

name: American Truck Simulator
description: The latest truck driving simulator in development by SCS Software.

name: Call of Duty: World at War
description: Treyarch takes the famous series back sixty years, with the first Call of Duty game set in the Pacific Theatre, against the Imperial Japanese in World War II.

name: Crossout
description: A post-apocalyptic massively multiplayer online car combat game.

name: Dofus
description: Created by Ankama Game, Dofus is a 2D MMORPG using a turn based battle system and features 15 unique classes.  The game has a charming artistic aesthetic instead of a realistic 3D world.

name: Comedy Night
description: An Xbox Indie game that allows players to take the stage or participate in lauding or loathing those up in front of the brick wall.

name: Enter the Gungeon
description: A top-down indie shooter with procedural level generation.

name: Elite Dangerous
description: The fourth entry in the Elite franchise, from the series' co-creator David Braben and Frontier Developments.

name: Wizard101
description: Wizard101 is a card-based fantasy MMO developed by KingIsle Entertainment.

name: AdVenture Capitalist
description: An incremental game where players start with setting up a lemonade stand and end up with managing oil companies.

name: Age of Empires II: HD Edition
aliases: Age of Empires II: The Conquerors

name: EVE Online
description: EVE Online is a loosely structured science fiction MMORPG published by CCP Games in which players take on the role of a spaceship pilot exploring a colonized galaxy.

name: Heat Signature
description: An open-world space mercenary roguelite from the developer of Gunpoint.

name: RimWorld
description: RimWorld is a colony-building game about a crash-landed space crew and their fight for survival.

name: WarThunder
description: War Thunder is a free-to-play air combat game set in the World War II and Korean War eras. Naval and land battles are planned additions.

name: Rivals of Aether
description: Rivals of Aether is an indie fighting game set in a vast world featuring a unique roster of elementally themed characters.

name: BeamNG.drive
description: Car sim developed by BeamNG.

name: Sid Meier's Civilization VI
description: The 6th mainline entry in the acclaimed 4X series.

name: The Elder Scrolls Online
description: An MMORPG set in the world of Nirn, focusing on the familiar continent of Tamriel, taking place a thousand years before The Elder Scrolls: Skyrim.

name: DOOM
description: In a world with health regeneration and cover-based systems, one of the longest-running first-person shooter series returns to its brutal, fast-paced roots.

name: Realm of the Mad God
description: A free-to-play, online 8-bit MMORPG hack-n-slash that brings you back to when RPGs were simpler, if there ever was a time.

name: Just Cause 3
description: Battle a dictator's forces in a fictional Mediterranean archipelago in this follow-up to the popular series from Avalanche Studios and Square-Enix.

name: Portal
description: A first-person puzzle game developed by Valve and graduates of DigiPen, Portal forces a human test subject to run a gauntlet of grueling spatial experiments administered by a malfunctioning, psychotic artificial intelligence named GLaDOS.

name: FIFA 17
description: EA's association football game for 2016 runs on the Frostbite engine.

name: DRAGON BALL XENOVERSE 2
description: A second time-traveling romp through the DragonBall series.

name: Friday the 13th: The Game
description: Take control of classic horror icon Jason Voorhees and stalk up to seven other players (as camp counselors trying to survive the night) in this asymmetrical-multiplayer survival horror game.

name: Prison Architect
description: The latest game announced by acclaimed indie developer, Introversion Software, in which players will "build and manage a maximum security prison." It is current available on Steam and through the developer's website.

name: TEKKEN 7
description: Tekken 7 is the final chapter of the Mishima family's storyline.

name: The Escapists 2
description: Sequel to The Escapists

name: Crusader Kings II
description: The sequel to Paradox Interactive's Crusader Kings is a grand strategy game that focuses mostly on the dynasties of medieval Europe. Games begin as early as 769 and can span until 1453. Expansions have expanded the game's scope to include the Middle East, India and the Eurasian Steppe.

name: Warface
description: A free-to-play, online first-person shooter developed and published by Crytek.

name: Middle-earth: Shadow of Mordor
description: An open-world action-adventure game by Monolith, set between the events of The Hobbit and The Lord of the Rings.

name: METAL GEAR SOLID V: THE PHANTOM PAIN
aliases: Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain
description: The seventh entry in the Metal Gear Solid series recounts the adventures of Punished 'Venom' Snake, as he wakes up from a nine-year coma in 1984 to rebuild his mercenary paradise.

name: Idle Champions of the Forgotten Realms
description: An idle game using the Dungeons & Dragons license.

name: HuniePop
description: HuniePop is a dating sim featuring puzzles and RPG-like systems.

name: Ultimate Chicken Horse
description: Ultimate Chicken Horse is a party platformer for up to four people where the players place platforms, traps and hazards and try to make the level too difficult for their friends, but easy enough for them.

name: NieR:Automata
description: NieR: Automata is an action RPG developed by PlatinumGames.

name: DARK SOULS II: Scholar of the First Sin
aliases: DARK SOULSâ„¢ II: Scholar of the First Sin
description: A remastered release of Dark Souls II, featuring a graphical upgrade, increased online player limit, remixed locations for items and enemies, and includes all of the previously released DLC.

name: Total War: WARHAMMER II
description: Total War: Warhammer II

name: Skullgirls
description: Take control of fierce female warriors in a 1940s dark Deco world in this stylish indie fighting game developed by (and for) hardcore fighting game enthusiasts.

name: Farming Simulator 17
description: The newest game in the Farming Simulator franchise for consoles and the PC.

name: 100% Orange Juice
description: A combination of board game and deck building that has players battling for stars and collecting cards.

name: Crypt of the NecroDancer
description: Enter the dungeons of dance and fight enemies to the beat of the music.

name: Call of Duty: Black Ops II
aliases: Call of Duty: Black Ops II - Multiplayer
description: The Black Ops storyline continues, switching the past Cold War from the game's predecessor to future 2025, as a new Cold War between U.S.A. and China flares up due to the actions of one vengeful drug-runner.

name: Sonic Adventure 2
description: Sonic Adventure 2 is a 2001 sequel to Sonic Adventure. It marks the debut appearance of Shadow the Hedgehog and Rouge the Bat, and is the first ever Sonic title where Dr. Eggman is playable.

name: Bloons TD Battles
description: A monkey themed tower defense game by.  Ninja Kiwi

name: Dishonored
description: After the Empress is killed, her most loyal bodyguard, Corvo, becomes the prime suspect, and must track down those who murdered his charge and betrayed him in order to enact his bloody revenge.

name: Sven Co-op
description: Sven Co-Op was originally a half-life mod allowing players to play through the Half-Life campaign and a selection of custom maps cooperatively. On July 16th, 2013 it was announced that it would be coming to Steam with Valve's blessing as a stand alone game.

name: Tower Unite
description: A unique take on an MMO that combines customization of a condo, character customization, several minigames, and a plaza that has many activities on its own.

name: Dying Light
description: Dying Light is a first-person, open world game set in a zombie apocalypse. The player character is able to free-run to get around the environment quickly.

name: Chivalry: Medieval Warfare
description: Chivalry: Medieval Warfare is a first-person, multiplayer-only, hack-and-slash sequel to the Age of Chivalry mod for Half-Life 2.

name: Squad
description: Squad is a modern military First Person Shooter for PC that focuses on teamwork oriented gameplay and large scale combined arms warfare, it is a spiritual sequel to the Project Reality modification for Battlefield 2.

name: ASTRONEER
description: Build and survive on procedural planets in this space exploration game from indie developer System Era Softworks.

name: Creativerse
description: Creativerse is a sandbox voxel adventure game. It features an RPG crafting system, layered biomes and is persistently online.

name: Oddworld: Abe's Oddysee
description: The first game in the Oddworld series. Players control an alien slave named Abe on a quest to free his fellow Mudokons from the clutches of Molluck, the ruthless boss of RuptureFarms.

name: Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon Wildlands
description: Take on South American drug cartels in the latest entry in the Ghost Recon franchise.

name: Warhammer: End Times - Vermintide
description: Mixing the grimdark fantasy world of Warhammer with the co-operative horde-slaying gameplay of the Left 4 Dead series, Vermintide pits a ragtag group of heroes against an endless army of the underground-dwelling Skaven.

name: BattleBlock Theater
description: Players are shipwrecked on a mysterious island and then forced to partake in deadly "performances" for the entertainment of a crowd of cats.

name: Killing Floor
description: When hordes of failed super-soldiers (the zombie-like "specimens") break out of the labs of Horzine Biotech, it's up to London's finest to put them down in this cooperative survival horror wave-based first-person shooter.

name: Kerbal Space Program
description: Players create their own rockets from a variety of parts and then attempt to launch them into space.

name: Rise of the Tomb Raider
description: A follow up to 2013's Tomb Raider reboot. After the events of the previous game, Lara spends one year searching to explain what she saw. Her quest to explain immortality leads her to Siberia, home of a mythical city known as Kitezh.

name: Castle Crashers
description: Grab three other knights and storm enemy forces in this downloadable beat-em-up for the Xbox 360, PlayStation 3, and PC, complete with smoothly-drawn graphics and action RPG elements.

name: Infestation: The New Z
description: Infestation: The New Z is an official reedition of Infestation: Survivor Stories, a zombie-apocalypse survival MMO PvP game. As its predecessor, it is set in Colorado and California with huge maps where players fight each other while trying to survive the zombie apocalypse.

name: Mirage: Arcane Warfare
description: From Torn Banner Studios, creators of Chivalry: Medieval Warfare, Mirage: Arcane Warfare is a magic and melee-focused multiplayer FPS. Expected to release in 2016

name: Fistful of Frags
description: Fistful of Frags is a multiplayer wild-west themed modification for Half Life 2. The game features various guns from the time period. The game has gone through Steam Greenlight and as of May 9, 2014, has become a standalone product on Steam.

name: STAR WARS Battlefront II
description: EA's second Star Wars Battlefront features cross-era characters and locations from the original, prequel and sequel Star Wars movie trilogies. It also includes multiplayer character classes and a story-driven single-player campaign.

name: Cuphead
description: A 2D co-op shooter-platformer focused on boss battles. It is known for its unique art style, which imitates the more surreal cartoons of the 1930s.

name: NARUTO SHIPPUDEN: Ultimate Ninja STORM 4
description: The Naruto series jumps to eighth generation consoles with the fourth sequential installment of the Ultimate Ninja Storm series.

name: TERA
description: TERA: The Exiled Realm of Arborea is a free-to-play, action-style MMORPG, developed by Bluehole Studios in South Korea using Unreal Engine 3. It was localized for English audiences by En Masse Entertainment of Seattle.

name: Absolver
description: Absolver is an online multiplayer combat game where players are placed behind the mask of a Prospect under control of the Guides, the new rulers of the fallen Adal Empire, who will determine your worth in joining their elite corps of Absolvers.

name: Total War: WARHAMMER
description: Creative Assembly's strategy series takes on Games Workshop's WARHAMMER.

name: Scrap Mechanic
description: A building game about a stranded mechanic on a farming moon.

name: Oxygen Not Included
description: A space colony simulation from Klei Entertainment.

name: Half-Life
description: Take on the role of Gordon Freeman as he escapes the disastrous aftermath of an experiment gone wrong in the Black Mesa Research Facility.

name: Nuclear Throne
description: A procedurally generated roguelike action game developed by Vlambeer. After creating a prototype called Wasteland Kings for Mojam 2, Vlambeer took the prototype and renamed it Nuclear Throne.

name: No More Room in Hell

developers.name: No More Room in Hell Team

description: A free co-operative zombie survival experience which started out as a Half-Life 2 mod that eventually turned to its own stand-alone game.

name: The Sims 3
description: Electronic Arts follows up to the hugely successful Sims 2 with an improved character creation system, an open neighborhood, and a greater focus on character development.

name: Divinity: Original Sin Enhanced Edition
description: Divinity: Original Sin is a top-down turn-based RPG developed by Larian Studios. It introduces new elements to the franchise, such as co-op gameplay and decision-making as well as a more interactive world.

name: Ravenfield
description: Ravenfield is a singleplayer battlefield style game. It started out as an experiment with ragdolls and AI, and will remain a slightly experimental, for-fun game project.

name: Life is Strange
description: An episodic adventure game based around time manipulation from Remember Me developers DONTNOD.

name: Planet Coaster
description: A theme park simulator from Frontier Developments, the creators of Roller Coaster Tycoon 3.

name: Dishonored 2
description: Set fifteen years after the end of the first game, Dishonored 2 allows players to continue the story as either original protagonist Corvo Attano or his daughter and apprentice, the now-deposed Empress Emily Kaldwin.
